# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Example environment configuration.
#
#   cp .env.example .env      then fill in / uncomment what you need.
#
# Everything here is OPTIONAL — the app builds and runs with sensible US
# defaults and the pledge wall stays dormant until its vars are all set.
# See README.md ("Configuration" and "Community pledge wall") for details.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- Crisis resource (build-time, client) ----------------------------------
# Shown when the distress index crosses the crisis threshold. Override for
# non-US deployments.
# VITE_CRISIS_LABEL="988 Suicide & Crisis Lifeline (U.S.)"
# VITE_CRISIS_BODY="If the weight feels like too much to hold right now, please talk to someone today. In the U.S., call or text 988, any hour. Outside the U.S., contact your local crisis line or a trusted clinician."

# --- CLE/CE provider fields (build-time, client) ---------------------------
# Populate the certificate and accreditation packet. Set these before
# offering the course for credit.
# VITE_PROVIDER_NAME="[Your organization name]"
# VITE_PROVIDER_NUMBER="[Provider/sponsor number — obtain from each board]"
# VITE_COURSE_AUTHOR="[Author / faculty name]"
# VITE_COURSE_AUTHOR_QUALS="[Author qualifications / bio]"
# VITE_PROVIDER_CONTACT="[Provider contact email]"

# --- Pledge wall backend (server-side, Vercel Functions) -------------------
# The wall stays OFF until the table name, region, and both credentials are
# present. Never commit real credentials — set these in your host's env.
# PLEDGE_DDB_TABLE="your-dynamodb-table-name"
# AWS_REGION="us-east-1"
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID="your-access-key-id"
# AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY="your-secret-access-key"
# PLEDGE_IP_SALT="optional-salt-for-the-rate-limiter-ip-hash"
